This paper deals with the complexity of infinite games with quantitative winning conditions, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between lookahead and the quality of winning strategies, which is a topic that falls under the scope of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves the study of automata and decision problems, which are topics that fall under the scope of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also touches upon formal languages, which is a topic that falls under the scope of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
